50|$|Despite the region's aridity, Mani {{is known}} for its unique culinary {{products}} such as glina or <b>syglino</b> (pork or pork sausage smoked with aromatic herbs such as thyme, oregano, mint, etc. and stored in lard along with orange peel). Mani is also known for what some consider the world's best extra-virgin olive oil, soft-pressed from partially ripened olives of the Koroneiki variety, which are grown on mountain terraces. The local honey is also of superior quality.|$|E

